post_text:
Happy Earth Day, Eastpointe fam! üåé
.
Earth Day started 50 years ago to give a voice to the public's growing concern for the earth and our environment. What a blessing!
.
In honor of Earth Day, we wanted to share this beautiful drawing of an eagle by one of our Art students. The eagle is a beautiful and strong animal that represents bravery and freedom. This seems so fitting for the tough times we are facing right now.
.
Thank you to Angel Marie for allowing us to share your beautiful and inspiring work of art.
.
"Golden Eagle"
Angel Marie, age 15
Media: Prismacolor pencil on paper
Image courtesy of the artist.
.
#EarthDay #EHS #EastpointeHighSchool #Tucson #EHSArt #BeBrave #BeFree #LoveTheEarth

I don‚Äôt know who is more excited. I am so pleased to announce the first graduate from the Tucson Rise Up Program. May 14, 2018 at 8:00 PM ¬∑

Starting May 29, free (yes, FREE) accelerated 8-week Math Bridge classes. Improve your essential math skills, gain the confidence and skills to improve your scores on the Accuplacer placement test or pass the GED test, and learn strategies to help you succeed in college. Deadline to sign up is May 25. For information, pcc-mathbridge@pima.edu, or 206-6557.

On this week of Thanksgiving, please join us in saying a big thank you to Arizona‚Äôs incredible educators. In every corner of our great state are educators who work passionately and tirelessly to help prepare our kids for success. Their work is vital to the strength of our state and our overall quality of life.

As we enjoy this holiday with friends and family and reflect on what we are most thankful for in our lives, let us all remember our teachers and consider what we can do in the coming year to show them our gratitude, respect, and support.

We wish all of you a very happy Thanksgiving!

post_text:
Fare Required to Ride, 10.14.13

Now that the major issues with the SunGO system have been resolved, all passengers are required to pay the appropriate fare starting Monday, October 14th.

As a reminder, riders may pay their fare one of the following ways:

Pass, value or transfer on a valid SunGO Card or SunGO ID & Card
Valid pass on a SunGO Ticket
Valid transfer on a SunGO Transfer Ticket
Economy cash fare, presented with valid SunGO ID & Card
Economy 30 Day Ticket, with a valid SunGO ID & Card
Cash at the full fare rate, if the rider does not have a valid SunGO ID & Card

Without a valid SunGO Card, ticket or transfer, a one-way cash fare is required starting October 14th. Those with an invalid SunGO ID & Card must pay the full fare. We appreciate your patience through the transition of the SunGO system.

post_text:
Welcome to Eastpointe High School!

Eastpointe offers a unique approach to education by engaging students with challenging curriculum that is aligned with Arizona Common Core Standards. We ensure to provide this service to all our students while maintaining a safe and scholarly environment.

At Eastpointe High School we understand that all of our students have a diverse range of needs when it comes to experiencing success in a high school setting. For that reason EPHS has developed a schedule, which offers every student that opportunity to experience success in school. Students attend school five days a week for four hours a day, with three convenient start times beginning at 7:30am, 9:40am and 11:50am.
